<h1>Common Diseases after 65</h1>

<ol>
    <li>
        <strong>Heart Disease</strong>
        <p>Heart disease is a common concern in older adults. Tests may include:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Cholesterol panel</li>
            <li>Electrocardiogram (ECG or EKG)</li>
            <li>Stress test</li>
        </ol>
    </li>

    <li>
        <strong>Osteoporosis</strong>
        <p>A condition where bones become brittle and fragile. Recommended tests:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Bone density test (DEXA scan)</li>
        </ol>
    </li>

    <li>
        <strong>Diabetes</strong>
        <p>High blood sugar levels can lead to diabetes. Tests include:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Glucose tolerance test</li>
            <li>HbA1c test</li>
        </ol>
    </li>

    <!-- Add more diseases with details and recommended tests -->

    <li>
        <strong>Arthritis</strong>
        <p>Joint inflammation and stiffness. Tests may include:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Joint fluid analysis</li>
            <li>X-rays</li>
        </ol>
    </li>

    <li>
        <strong>Alzheimer's Disease</strong>
        <p>A progressive neurological disorder. Diagnosis often involves:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Neuropsychological tests</li>
            <li>Brain imaging (MRI, CT scan)</li>
        </ol>
    </li>

    <li>
        <strong>Colon Cancer</strong>
        <p>Risk increases with age. Screening tests include:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Colonoscopy</li>
            <li>Fecal occult blood test (FOBT)</li>
        </ol>
    </li>

    <li>
        <strong>Pneumonia</strong>
        <p>An inflammatory condition of the lung affecting older adults. Tests may include:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Chest X-ray</li>
            <li>Blood tests</li>
        </ol>
    </li>

    <li>
        <strong>Macular Degeneration</strong>
        <p>An eye disease causing vision loss. Tests include:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Eye exam</li>
            <li>Fluorescein angiography</li>
        </ol>
    </li>

</ol>